============================================
Q. @Component vs @Service vs @Repository ?
===========================================

@Component — for general-purpose beans that don’t fit Service/Repository/Controller (utilities, helpers, configuration beans not created with @Bean).
If none of the other stereotypes fit, use @Component

@Service — for classes that implement business logic, orchestration between DAOs and controllers, transactions at service level.
Use it for core domain behavior.

@Repository — for classes that directly talk to the database (JPA repositories, DAOs, JDBC).
Use it when your class encapsulates persistence code. Spring can apply exception translation here.



